structures.label: Sermons for the Common of the Saints
Sermons for the Proper of the Saints

description: CCCC MS 336 dates to the first half of the fifteenth century and contains a collection of Lollard sermons. This collection includes sets 2 (on the Common of the Saints), 3 (on the Proper of the Saints) and 4 (on the ferial gospels) of the Wycliffite sermon cycle which is preserved in a number of manuscripts.
